</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3796656070D7FF31FF23EBCC89F2F984" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70D7FF31FF23EBCC89F2F984" blockId="169.[151,1436,1397,1602]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FF23EBCC8B44FA77" bold="true" box="[199,335,1433,1458]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D7FF31FEBCEBCC880CFA74" author="Dlussky, G. M." box="[344,519,1433,1457]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" pagination="616 - 627" refId="ref110477" refString="Dlussky, G. M. (1997) Genera of ants from Baltic Amber. Paleontological Journal, 31 (6), 616 - 627." type="journal article" year="1997">Dlussky (1997)</bibRefCitation>
postulated that this species likely did not belong in 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FBBAEBCC8EE4FA74" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[1118,1263,1433,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FBBAEBCC8EE4FA74" box="[1118,1263,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and that it “… most probably should be placed into another genus …” However, he did not erect a new genus for it as he only had 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70D7FF31FF73EBB48B61FA3C" author="Wheeler, W. M." box="[151,362,1505,1529]" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref113081" refString="Wheeler, W. M. (1915 b) The ants of the Baltic Amber. Schriften der Physikalisch-okonomischen Gesellschaft zu Konigsberg in Pr., 55 (1914), 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1915">Wheeler’s (1915b)</bibRefCitation>
drawing available and did not feel this was sufficient to establish a new genus. It is clear that this species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FDE1E850889DF9D8" baseAuthorityName="Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="1990" box="[517,662,1541,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FDE1E850889DF9D8" box="[517,662,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is, in fact, so distinct that assignment to a separate, and new, genus seems straightforward. This genus, 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870D7FF31FD89E87C890FF984" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" box="[621,772,1577,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eldermyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="169" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970D7FF31FD89E87C890FF984" box="[621,772,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="169" pageNumber="170">Eldermyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is established above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
